fields.title: backend engineer
fields.specification:
• Apply a variety of testing techniques to validate new features.
  • Create detailed, comprehensive and well-structured test plans and test cases
  • Develop and apply testing processes for new and existing products to meet product needs
  • Responsible for development, execution, tracking and results reporting of manual test cases for assigned projects/features using Microsoft Visual Studio/Team Foundation Server
  • Estimating, prioritizing, planning and coordinating quality testing activities
  • Participate in daily stand-up and weekly sprint planning Meeting
  • Determine and estimate QA/QC tasks during Sprint Planning
  • Ability to perform assigned tasks and complete work on schedule with minimal
fields.requirement:
• Develops and executes basic/complex SQL queries
  • An understanding of SDLC concepts
  • Solid knowledge of Object Oriented Programming Concept
  • Ability to communicate clearly and effectively with USA Team.
  • Ability to lead independently and as part of a team
  • Knowledge of bug tracking tool and automation testing tools will be an advantage
fields.benefit:
• Attractive salary
  • Provident Fund
  • Gratuity Bonus
  • Medical and Accidental insurance
  • Open International Work Environment
  • 5 Working Days per Week
  • Festival Expense Allowance
  • Paid Paternity, Maternity, Marriage, Sick and Casual Leave
